content.description: Begin on the left arete and traverse right and up, topping out to the left of the right arete.
content.location: The route 10 feet left of Beam Me Up (V2) in the Rubik's Cube section of Forest

content.description: High ball (can be top roped) delicate face climbing using the small seams and arête
content.protection: Two bolts on top - top rope recommended
content.location: Upper west parking area, the last pullout on the corner before you reach the end of the road. This problem is on the back side of the huge boulder sitting right in front of you if you hiked the new trail. Around the corner from West Forest Arete (Beam Me Up)

content.description: Fun arete, slightly overhanging with plentiful good holds.  Sit start on obvious low block move up to crimps and side pulls then either go left or right around the arete (both are similarly easy) and grab the point (it's a jug) and turn the top.
content.location:
Upper west parking area, the last pullout on the corner before you reach the end of the road. This problem is on the back side of the huge boulder sitting right in front of your car if you parked in the right place. Follow the trail into the woods and look right as you reach the back of the huge boulder.

On the north side of a small boulder a short walk uphill from Equinox.
